        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 1. Parathyone itapuaensis sp. nov., holotype MZUSP 2089. (a) specimen in dorsal view; (b) detail of the tentaclesand mouth in frontal view; (c) anal papillae (white arrow); (d) Polian vesicle (yellow arrow), longitudinal muscle (white arrow), stomach (green arrow) and calcareous ring (red arrow); (e) longitudinal muscle split anteriorly; (f) attachment of the longitudinal muscle at the anterior processes of the calcareous ring; (g) rm: retractor muscle, madreporite (red arrow) and stone canal (yellow arrow); (h) Polian vesicle (yellow arrow) and (i) photograph of the calcareous ring in outer view (rma: retractor muscle attachment, lma: longitudinal muscle attachment." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4943529/files/figure.png" .

